Pydantic has an interesting behavior where the following field declaration is considered required but also allowed to be `None`:

```python
some_field: Optional[str] = Field(..., description="The ... means it has no default")
```

The current behavior of FastAPI is to treat the field as non-nullable required, i.e.

```json
{
    "properties": {
        "some_field": {
            "type": "string"
        }
    },
    "required": ["some_field"]
}
```

Clients generated from this will fail with an error if the service ever returns `some_field: null`.

This PR adds some code to check if a field is both required and nullable, and change it to the following:

```json
{
    "properties": {
        "some_field": {
            "nullable": true,
            "type": "string"
        }
    },
    "required": ["some_field"]
}
```

